post_text:
Kaneland CUSD #302 is currently seeking qualified candidates for school bus drivers for the 2020-2021 school year.

Must have a valid driver’s license, a CDL with a school bus endorsement is preferred. If you currently hold a CDL with a school bus endorsement we are offering a $500 Sign-On Bonus incentive, with an additional $500 AFTER your first year of Service. Kaneland does offer on-site training if a bus endorsement is needed.

Daily hours are approximately 6:00 a.m. - 7:30 a.m. and 2:00 p.m. - 4:00 p.m. for a Single route which is what we have available at this time. Pay is competitive.

To apply, please visit:
https://phl.applitrack.com/D302/onlineapp/jobpostings/view.asp?&all=1&category=Support+Staff

post_text:
Here is the March 20 letter in spanish.

20 de marzo de 2020

Familias de Kaneland:

¿Ustedes necesitan recoger algo de la escuela?

Con el cierre tan rápido de nuestras escuelas el viernes 13 de marzo de 2020 y el cierre de la escuela hasta el 7 de abril de 2020, queremos darles al personal y a las familias la oportunidad de recoger materiales académicos y pertenencias de los alumnos de sus aulas o casilleros (lockers). Todas las escuelas de Kaneland estarán abiertas mañana sábado 21 de marzo de 9:00 a.m. a 12:00 p.m.



Entren solo a través de las entradas principales: un administrador estará en cada escuela si tiene alguna pregunta. Recuerden practicar el distanciamiento social, y para los grados 6-12 envíe solo a su estudiante a la escuela. Para los estudiantes de primaria, todos los estudiantes deben tener un padre que los acompañe al edificio.

Más información de toda la escuela seguirá esta noche o mañana.

Orgulloso de ser un Knight,



Administración de Kaneland

post_text:
March 20, 2020

Kaneland Families:

Do You Need To Get Something From School?
With our schools being closed so quickly last Friday, March 13, 2020, and the school closure continuing until April 7, 2020, we want to give staff and families an opportunity to collect academic materials and student belongings from their classrooms and/or lockers. All Kaneland schools will be open tomorrow, Saturday March 21 from 9:00 am - 12:00 pm.

Please enter through the main entrances only - an administrator will be at each school should you have any questions. Please remember to practice social distancing and for grades 6-12 send only your student into the school. For the elementary school students, all students should have a parent accompany them into the building.

More school-wide information will follow tonight or tomorrow.

Proud to be a Knight,

Kaneland Administration

post_text:
Celebrating Kaneland 2020 - Digital Gallery Walk

Over the past four years, the district has taken great strides to shift our learning practices and connect as a community.

This week, we will highlight some of the ways our students are learning. Joins us in celebrating Kaneland 2020 and get a peek into the world of a Kaneland Knight.

Student Empowerment Through Goal Setting
By Tiffany Reuter and Nancy Meisenger

Students set a goal through a conference with the teacher. They have their checklists to use and refer to each writing session. The students can monitor their progress by using the checklist and the teacher can provide feedback by coloring in a smiley face when students show they are meeting their goal. Students can track progress as they work on this goal in several writing pieces. If students meet their goal, the teacher and student will conference to set a new goal.

Watch our short video on 1st Grade Writing Goals: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rmR-LeopT38&feature=youtu.be

Kaneland 302 School District is pleased to announce the early childhood center at Blackberry Creek Elementary will continue to serve as a learning environment for all district preschool-aged children for the 2020-2021 school year with our highly qualified early childhood faculty.

Classes run Monday-Thursday morning (8:50-11:15) and afternoon (12:50-3:20). Transportation is parent responsibility.

We will accept interest applications beginning February 22, 2020, at the Young Knight's Fair (Forms will post in all Kaneland school virtual backpacks on February 24, 2020) No registration fees or documents needed at the time of interest application submission. Deadline for applications: March 17, 2020

If a lottery is needed, it will be held on March 19, 2020, with notification to families to follow. Total anticipated registration cost: $385.00 will be due May 1, 2020, to secure your child's spot for fall.

As part of our 1:1 Initiative, we are pleased to offer a new resource for our parents. The Student Tech Profile allows parents to track devices and see how their students are utilizing their Chromebook. The profile link is https://www.kaneland.org/r/tech-profile and is now available under the Parent tab on any of our websites.

Phase I which allows parents to see device details, repair history, and handbook information is live now. Phase II shows parents their student's screentime and most frequently used apps and websites. This will be live in 2020.

We hope you enjoy this new resource.

Families, researchers, policymakers, and community members can use the site to find school data, including academic performance, school environment, educators, students, and highlights provided by principals.

We have also updated our Indicators of Success web page with the latest data. That page can be accessed under the 'About' section or our website, or via the link below.

Maple Park, IL - The Kaneland Foundation is a non-profit organization that has contributed for decades to the educational needs of the students of Kaneland District #302. Our mission is to support academic excellence through innovation. Since the Kaneland Foundation has no administrative costs, every dollar goes back to our students in the Kaneland District.

Please consider joining us at the Kaneland Foundation Annual Golf Outing on Thursday, September 19, 2019 at Bliss Creek Golf Course in Sugar Grove. Feel free to contact Beth Sterkel at 630-365-8295 or beth.sterkel@kaneland.org with questions you may have about the Kaneland Foundation, https://foundation.kaneland.org/, or to have a registration form mailed or e-mailed to you. Electronic registration on the Kaneland Store, https://kaneland.revtrak.net/Kaneland-Foundation/KF-Golf-Outing/#/list, opened on July 01 allowing you to register and pay electronically.

We are truly grateful for your support to the Foundation and thank you for your sponsorship and participation in the golf outing.

Every day, 43 children are diagnosed with cancer and each year, over 40,000 children are treated for cancer. No child should ever have to fight cancer, they should be enjoying their childhood! To help bring an end to pediatric cancer, Kaneland High School is going GOLD with Cal’s Angels to raise awareness for pediatric cancer and the gold ribbon.

Our goal is to turn Kaneland High School GOLD during September. If you attend an athletic event during September, you will see gold accessories on our athletes that were provided by Cal’s Angels. We will also be selling t-shirts for $10 during lunch hours this Wednesday Thursday and Friday to wear to our Gold Out Football Game on August 30th.

The Kaneland Board of Education (BOE) and the Kaneland Education Association (KEA) are pleased to announce that they have ratified a Collective Bargaining Agreement for five years covering the 2019-2020 through the 2023-2024 school years. The 6-0 vote was taken on August 5, 2019, by the BOE at a special Board of Education meeting. Ninety-nine percent of the Kaneland Education Association voted on Thursday, August 1, 2019, to ratify the contract.

The full press release is below.

Taste of Kaneland – Lots of Fun!

The Taste of Kaneland Committee has been busy planning and organizing for the event, to be held Sunday, August 25th from 3-7p.m. If you're interested in showcasing your talents for the Kaneland's Got Talent portion of the event, please direct your questions to Kanelandsgottalent@kaneland.org. Auditions will be held on July 28th and August 10th at the KHS auditorium.

Other events for the day include two obstacle courses and a human foosball game.

If you are interested in securing a booth to showcase your business, or would like to sponsor this event, please inquire at: 10161@kaneland.org.

All parents are invited and welcomed to attend the 1:1 learning implementation parent meeting. We are excited to begin the process of rolling out a Chromebook for each student in grades 4-12 beginning next year. At this parent meeting, the team will share the purpose, process, and key parent signature pages that must be completed.

Parents should plan to attend the meeting(s) that will focus on your student's grade level for the 2019-2020 school year (e.g. 3rd-grade parents should attend the 4/5 grade meeting).

Dates are as follows:

~April 22nd, 6:30 PM, Harter Middle School Cafeteria- Middle School Focus
~April 23rd, 6:30 PM, Kaneland High School Auditorium - High School Focus
~April 30th, 6:30 PM, Harter Middle School Cafeteria - Fourth/Fifth Grade Focus

Please bring your questions to the session. Students are also encouraged to attend this meeting to hear the process and responsibility. We look forward to a great session!

Kaneland D302's Department of Special Services will be hosting a Preschool Screening on April 12th.

District families that are interested should call Special Services at 630-365-4118 to sign up prior to the day of screening. Screenings will be held at Blackberry Creek Elementary and the screening is FREE.

Students of all ages from birth to preschool age would be able to receive information on their developmental levels, as well as determine if they are eligible to receive any specialized services to address developmental delays.

Because ticket sales for this year’s Pork Chop Dinner have been lower than anticipated, we have made the decision, in conjunction with the Elburn Lions Club, to cancel the Pork Chop Dinner fundraiser on Sunday, February 10, 2019. Sincerely,

School is CLOSED Monday, January 28, 2019

Dear Kaneland Parents,

Good evening, this is Kaneland District Administration writing with an important school closing message based on the winter weather advisory. After consultation with local authorities and our building maintenance staff, all Kaneland schools will be closed tomorrow, Monday, January 28, 2019. All school buildings will also be closed tomorrow - all school practices, competitions and activities are also canceled.

The administration will also continue to monitor the severe cold temperatures forecasted for this upcoming week. We will update parents in as timely a manner as possible with any cancellations or changes to the school schedule.

The Kaneland Board of Education is planning to meet as regularly scheduled at 7:00 p.m. at Harter Middle School on Monday, January 28, 2019.

If you must travel tomorrow, please be safe.

Kaneland District Administration

KANELAND.REVTRAK.NET
KHS Madrigal Feaste | Kaneland CUSD 302

Kaneland High School
November 4, 2018 at 10:26 PM ·

Wes Hale! Good Lords and Ladies fair!
We bid thee welcome, we bid thee share
Our feasting and our revelry,
Our music and our company!

These lines, spoken by the court jester, are meant to remind us that the holiday season is very near and the Madrigal Feaste is fast approaching. This is the 41st year of the Kaneland Music Department's Renaissance Dinner. Performances will be held at Kaneland High School in the cafeteria. Parking is reserved for attendees in the northeast corner of campus.

Tickets for the 2018 Madrigal Feaste are now on sale and are priced at $25.00 each. Dates and times are listed below. In the event that we are unable to seat you on the date of your first choice, we ask that you indicate an alternate date choice and provide an email address for ticket confirmation.

MADRIGAL FEASTE PERFORMANCES
Friday December 7, 2018 @ 7:00 PM
Saturday December 8, 2018 @ 2:00 PM
Saturday December 8, 2018 @ 7:00 PM
Sunday December 9, 2018 @ 2:00 PM

Tickets are available now at the Webstore:

https://kaneland.revtrak.net/KHS/KHS-Madrigal-Feaste/#/list
